102
00:05:56,261 --> 00:05:57,527
-Is that so?

103
00:05:57,561 --> 00:05:59,427
-Uh-huh.

104
00:05:59,461 --> 00:06:02,327
I imagine Rukia is happy
on the other side as well.

105
00:06:02,361 --> 00:06:05,127
She probably has friends
and family waiting for her.

106
00:06:10,661 --> 00:06:12,127
-I have to go and
bring her back.

107
00:06:12,161 --> 00:06:16,127
-But why should you bring her
back if she's happy there.

108
00:06:16,161 --> 00:06:17,961
-Because I know she's
in serious trouble,

109
00:06:17,994 --> 00:06:20,461
and they just might kill her
if I don't get her out in time.

110
00:06:26,227 --> 00:06:28,661
-Here's what the
Ichigo I know would do.

111
00:06:28,694 --> 00:06:31,961
Hmm, he'd make a mad face
and tell Rukia she can always

112
00:06:31,994 --> 00:06:34,561
visit with friends and
family later if she lives,

113
00:06:34,594 --> 00:06:38,861
but she won't have that
chance if she's dead.

114
00:06:38,894 --> 00:06:42,227
I bet you've already made
up your mind, haven't you?

115
00:06:42,261 --> 00:06:42,727
[giggles]

116
00:06:49,961 --> 00:06:52,327
-You really were here.

117
00:06:52,361 --> 00:06:53,894
I know that.

118
00:06:53,927 --> 00:06:55,894
And you belong here, Rukia.

119
00:06:58,927 --> 00:06:59,794
Thanks a lot, Orihime.

120
00:07:08,961 --> 00:07:11,361
-Huh?

121
00:07:11,394 --> 00:07:11,861
Chad.

122
00:07:14,794 --> 00:07:16,694
[meowing]

123
00:07:26,961 --> 00:07:29,827
-I still can't believe Ichigo
would take off on a summer

124
00:07:29,861 --> 00:07:32,527
vacation and leave
the rest of us behind.

125
00:07:32,561 --> 00:07:33,227
-Grow up, Yuzu.

126
00:07:33,261 --> 00:07:34,427
He's always taking off.

127
00:07:34,461 --> 00:07:35,861
